      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:33.745172+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The new MobiLipid library contains 377 DTCCSN2 values for 162 U13C-labeled lipids detected at lipid species level across 15 lipid classes... The full DTCCSN2 library for U13C-labeled yeast lipids is provided in the Supporting Information (Table S1).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper provides the DTCCSN2 library with structure and lipid class coverage details (Table S1 in SI), but the card's framing as a 'validation report' is not explicitly described as an output. The paper presents library curation criteria and quality checks (mass accuracy \u22645 ppm, detection in \u22652 samples, CCS RSD <1%), but does not frame these as a formal 'validation report' output. The library itself and its statistics are documented, but not as a standalone validation report artifact.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01253",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validation report documenting DTCCSN2 library structure, lipid class coverage, CCS value statistics, and conformance to specifications",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:33.745172+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'reproducing' the DTCCSN2 library, but the paper presents the library as already established and curated by the authors. The research question asks about the structure and coverage of the library 'as provided with MobiLipid,' which is descriptive/analytical rather than generative.",
        "The card does not mention the key methodological requirement: the library was derived from LC-DTIM-MS measurements of U13C-labeled yeast extract (Komagataella phaffii). Reproducing the library would require access to this specific labeled biomass and DTIM-MS instrumentation.",
        "The card does not specify the curation criteria (mass accuracy \u22645 ppm, detection in \u22652 samples, coelution of adducts, CCS RSD <1%) that were applied to filter the library entries, which are central to understanding the library's quality and reproducibility."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:39:33.745172+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MobiLipid is run in the R studio environment... By spiking U13C-labeled lipids into measured samples and determination of the CCSN2 bias between derived CCS values and the DTCCSN2 library, the extent of the bias can be assessed for each measured data file",
      "asbval:note": "Research question directly addresses the core functionality of MobiLipid: calculating CCS bias using U13C-labeled internal standards.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01253",
