    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the mean bias before and after correction relative to library DTCCSN2 values for labeled lipids is computed and reported. ... the exemplary generated results, including all correction functions, corrected CCSN2 values, and CCSN2 bias before and after correction can be accessed in the Supporting Information (Tables S2\u2013S7).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports CCS bias metrics and provides tables, but these are presented as exemplary results for a specific dataset (TIM-MS data), not as a systematic analysis of bias quality as a function of lipid count. The paper does generate up to 100 correction functions using 3\u20136 lipids and reports bias distributions, but the primary output is not framed as a summary table of quality metrics indexed by lipid count.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01253",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
