    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/collision-cross-section-bias-quantification/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "By spiking U\u00b9\u00b3C-labeled lipids into measured samples and determination of the CCSN2 bias between derived CCS values and the DTCCSN2 library, the extent of the bias can be assessed for each measured data file, providing a straightforward approach to achieving constant quality control using lipid class-specific labeled internal standards.",
