      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "By spiking U13C-labeled lipids into measured samples and determination of the CCSN2 bias between derived CCS values and the DTCCSN2 library... The functions require a minimum of three labeled lipids as input for each lipid class-adduct combination.",
      "asbval:note": "Same issue as research_question: 'deuterated CCS library' is a misnomer. The actual library is DT CCS N2 for U13C-labeled lipids. The functional description is correct.",
