    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/lipid-class-coverage-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To ensure the quality of the library, only DTCCSN2 values fulfilling the following criteria were included: (1) high mass accuracy (\u22645 ppm error), (2) confirmed detection in at least two samples, (3) confirmed coelution of adducts, and (4) a CCS relative standard deviation <1%. Finally, the resulting DTCCSN2 values were verified by plotting the entries for each lipid class versus the respective m/z values (Figure 1A).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes validation of the DTCCSN2 library itself (quality control during library creation), not a separate task of validating an already-acquired library. The card describes a post-hoc validation workflow, whereas the paper describes the library curation process. The function is related but the scope differs: paper validates during library construction; card proposes validating an external library before use.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01253",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "lipid-class-coverage-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validates the structural completeness and CCS value distribution of a collision cross section (CCS) reference library for ion mobility-mass spectrometry lipidomics by verifying lipid class presence, extracting metadata, and confirming numeric ranges against documented specificati",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:43:32.328159+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/lipid-class-coverage-assessment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MobiLipid is a fully automated R Markdown tool utilizing a newly established DTCCSN2 library for U13C-labeled lipids to internally assess CCSN2 bias in IM-MS lipidomics workflows and allow CCS correction without the need for additional external calibration procedures.",
      "asbval:note": "MobiLipid uses the DTCCSN2 library for CCS bias assessment and correction, but the paper does not describe a separate validation workflow for verifying library completeness before use. MobiLipid applies the library; it does not validate it as a standalone task.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01253",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "lipid-class-coverage-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have acquired a CCS reference library (such as DTCCSN2 for U13C labeled lipids) and need to verify that it contains the expected lipid classes, CCS values are physically plausible for ion mobility data, and coverage matches the library's advertised documentation before u",
