      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MobiLipid is run in the R studio environment. Comprehensive documentation of required installations and how to run MobiLipid is provided at https://github.com/FelinaHildebrand/MobiLipid.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms R is used for MobiLipid implementation and data processing (e.g., 'further data filtering, evaluation, and visualization was done in the R studio programming environment'), but the specific role described in the card (library validation scripting) is not explicitly documented. R is used for CCS correction and bias calculation, not for independent library validation.",
