      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MobiLipid utilizes a newly established DT CCS N2 library for uniformly (U) 13 C-labeled lipids, derived from a U 13 C-labeled yeast extract, containing 377 DT CCS N2 values. This automated open-source R Markdown tool enables internal monitoring and straightforward compensation for CCS N2 biases.",
      "asbval:note": "MobiLipid provides and uses the DTCCSN2 library, but its primary role is CCS bias monitoring and correction, not library validation. The card describes MobiLipid as a source/distribution tool for validation purposes; the paper describes it as a tool for applying the library to correct CCS biases in experimental data.",
